OL,3,CSeveral GCSE and A-level exams could
OL,4,Cbe taken on screen from 2030
OL,6,FUnder the proposals, exam boards will
OL,7,Fnot be able to put forward on-screen
OL,8,Fexams in subjects taken by more than
OL,9,F100,000 pupils in a year, which
OL,10,Fincludes many of the main GCSE
OL,11,Fsubjects, as well as A-level maths.
OL,13,FOfqual chief regulator Sir Ian
OL,14,FBauckham told the Press Association:
OL,15,F"If any more on-screen assessment is
OL,16,Fgoing to happen, it needs to be done
OL,17,Fin a way which is managed and in the
OL,18,Finterests of students, commands public
OL,19,Fconfidence and is deliverable,
OL,20,Fimportantly, for schools and colleges."
